The paper deals with linear codes, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes have potential applications in cryptography (cs.CR) and secret sharing schemes (cs.DM). The codes are constructed using cyclotomy, which is a topic in algebraic coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the weight enumerator of the codes, which is a combinatorial object (cs.DM, cs.SI).
